        "setup": "Create a developer account in [The Bridge signup](https://bridge.setu.co/v2/signup). In [Bridge settings](https://docs.setu.co/dev-tools/bridge/settings), use **API credentials** to view test credentials; live credentials are generated after a product goes live. Some products also require onboarding with Setu: BBPS BillPay says to contact [onboarding@setu.co](mailto:onboarding@setu.co) to obtain `clientID`, `secret`, and `X-PARTNER-ID`. Use the product-specific instance identifier where required, such as `x-product-instance-id`.",
